menu "spangap: reticulum (rnsd)"

config SPANGAP_RNSD_JOBS_DEFER_PKTS
    int "Defer Transport::jobs() above this inbound-packet burst"
    range 0 1024
    default 8
    help
        The rnsd task runs Transport::jobs() — an unyieldy sweep of the path,
        link and receipt tables — on a ~2 s cadence. The sweep can park the
        task past the interfaces' 100 ms itsSend timeout, dropping inbound
        packets at RNSD_PORT_IFACE (visible as "ITS send dropped" warnings).

        When the number of packets received since the last sweep is at least
        this value, rnsd treats the task as busy (e.g. servicing a resource
        transfer) and defers the sweep to a later tick — up to
        SPANGAP_RNSD_JOBS_DEFER_MAX consecutive times. During such a burst the
        sweep has little essential work, so deferring it keeps the inbox
        draining and cuts the drops.

        Set to 0 to defer whenever any inbound traffic arrived since the last
        sweep. Raise it to make deferral kick in only under heavier load.

config SPANGAP_RNSD_JOBS_DEFER_MAX
    int "Max consecutive Transport::jobs() deferrals"
    range 0 32
    default 3
    help
        Upper bound on how many sweep-ticks in a row the jobs() sweep may be
        deferred under sustained load. Once this many deferrals accumulate the
        sweep runs regardless of load, so link keepalives, path-request
        retries and resource timeouts still fire within roughly
        (this + 1) x 2 s. Set to 0 to disable deferral entirely (always sweep).

endmenu
